                        <h4>Stock Alerts Logic</h4>
                        <p>Items in the "Inventory Intelligence" sidebar are flagged based on specific logic:</p>

                        <div class="guide-badge-example">
                            <span class="badge badge-danger">Critical: &lt; 3mo Supply</span>
                        </div>
                        <p>
                            <b>Trigger:</b> When an item has <b>less than 3 months of stock</b> remaining based on
                            its
                            current sales velocity.
                            <br><i>Calculation: (On Hand / Velocity) &lt; 3</i>
                        </p>

                        <div class="guide-badge-example">
                            <span class="badge badge-warn">Catalog &gt; 500</span>
                        </div>
                        <p>
                            <b>Trigger:</b> When an older title (released > 18 months ago) has over <b>500 units</b>
                            sitting in stock.
                            <br><i>Goal: Identify slow-moving catalog items incurring storage fees.</i>
                        </p>

                        <div class="guide-badge-example">
                            <span class="badge badge-warn">≤ 12mo &gt; 750</span>
                        </div>
                        <p>
                            <b>Trigger:</b> When a newer title (released within last year) has over <b>750
                                units</b>.
                            <br><i>Goal: Watchlist for potential overstock on recent releases.</i>
                        </p>
                    </div>

